Lagos State Government has confirmed it recorded 87 new cases of COVID-19 on Wednesday. The State Commissioner for Health, Prof Akin Abayomi, made this known via his Twitter page. He also confirmed that 49 patients have been discharged. Abayomi wrote, “COVID-19 Lagos Update as at 29th April, 2020 “87 new COVID-19 cases were confirmed in Lagos on April 29, 2020. Total number of confirmed cases in Lagos is now 947. “The good news is that 49 additional COVID-19 survivors have been discharged following their full recovery.” Meanwhile, Nigeria’s confirmed cases now stand at 1728. 